</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[701,1228,1413,1759]" lastBlockId="22.[93,620,213,1759]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="21" pageNumber="21">
Temminck (1824: livr. 49, pl. 293, fig. 2) based his name, 
<emphasis box="[905,1088,1442,1465]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName box="[905,1083,1442,1465]" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="speciosa">Sylvia speciosa</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
on a Wied manuscript name and pictured it in plate 293, figure 2. A specimen, RMNH 90238, is considered the 
<typeStatus box="[882,984,1531,1553]" pageId="21" pageNumber="21">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dekker and Quaiser, 2006: 37)" baseAuthorityName="Dekker and Quaiser" baseAuthorityPageNumber="37" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis box="[1028,1121,1532,1553]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="21">speciosa</emphasis>
(Dekker and Quaiser, 2006: 37)
</taxonomicName>
. Wied was generous in sending specimens to Temminck, already labeled with the names he intended to give them. Because Wied’s own publication was delayed for many years, Temminck’s use of some of the names Wied had written on his labels made Temminck the author of those names. In the description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Temminck" authorityName="Temminck" class="Aves" family="Sylviidae" genus="Sylvia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis box="[446,539,213,234]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">speciosa</emphasis>
, Temminck
</taxonomicName>
credits ‘‘P. Max’’ (5 Prince Maximilian) with the name. It seems logical that Temminck would have deposited the specimen used for the illustration in RMNH, where he was the director.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
However, AMNH 4352, male (on Wied label), collected in ‘‘Brasilia,’’ by Maximilian, Prince of Wied, was considered by Allen (1889: 217) to be the specimen used by Temminck for his illustration, but he credited 
<bibRefCitation author="Wied &amp; Maximilian, Prinz von" box="[93,299,535,557]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="637 - 1277" refId="ref131007" refString="Wied, Maximilian, Prinz von. 1831. Beitrage zur Naturgeschichte von Brasilien, 3 (2): 637 - 1277. Weimar: Gr. H. S. priv. Landes-Industrie-Comptoirs." type="journal article" year="1831">Wied (1831: 708)</bibRefCitation>
with the description. This cannot be correct, as Temminck’s description came out seven years prior to Wied’s publication. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wied &amp; Maximilian, Prinz von" box="[249,465,623,645]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="637 - 1277" refId="ref131007" refString="Wied, Maximilian, Prinz von. 1831. Beitrage zur Naturgeschichte von Brasilien, 3 (2): 637 - 1277. Weimar: Gr. H. S. priv. Landes-Industrie-Comptoirs." type="journal article" year="1831">Wied (1831: 710)</bibRefCitation>
said ‘‘ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Temminck</emphasis>
giebt, nach dem von mir ihm mitgetheilten Exemplare, eine ziemlich gute Abbildung dieser Species, wo aber die Beine und der Schnabel unrichtig colorirt sind.’’ This implies that Wied sent Temminck more than one specimen, and the 
<typeStatus box="[419,469,799,820]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
status of the AMNH specimen is unresolved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
Allen (1889: 217) gave the collecting locality of the AMNH specimen as 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, but that is the locality given by Temminck for the specimen he used. The locality on the Wied label on AMNH 4352 is given as ‘‘Brasilia’’ as is usual on Wied’s labels. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wied &amp; Maximilian, Prinz von" box="[181,446,1033,1055]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="637 - 1277" refId="ref131007" refString="Wied, Maximilian, Prinz von. 1831. Beitrage zur Naturgeschichte von Brasilien, 3 (2): 637 - 1277. Weimar: Gr. H. S. priv. Landes-Industrie-Comptoirs." type="journal article" year="1831">Wied (1831: 709–710)</bibRefCitation>
said that the species was not rare around 
<collectingRegion box="[441,619,1062,1084]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and that later he had found it the province of 
<collectingRegion box="[127,198,1121,1143]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, in the area of Angicos. Thus, it is not certain where the AMNH specimen was collected. The Wied label bears the number ‘‘139’’ written in pencil and of unknown significance. Allen did not find this species listed in Wied’s catalog.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
<bibRefCitation author="Hellmayr, C. E." box="[122,368,1297,1319]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" refId="ref119559" refString="Hellmayr, C. E. 1935. Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands. Alaudidae - Hirundinidae - Motacillidae - Bombycillidae - Ptilogonatidae - Dulidae - Vireonidae - Vireolaniidae - Cyclarhidae - Laniidae - Sturnidae - Coerebidae - Compsothlypidae. Chicago: Field Museum of Natural History, Publication 347, Zoological Series, volume 13, Part 8, vi + 541 pp." type="book" year="1935">Hellmayr (1935: 314)</bibRefCitation>
refers to 
<bibRefCitation author="Wied &amp; Maximilian, Prinz von" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="637 - 1277" refId="ref131007" refString="Wied, Maximilian, Prinz von. 1831. Beitrage zur Naturgeschichte von Brasilien, 3 (2): 637 - 1277. Weimar: Gr. H. S. priv. Landes-Industrie-Comptoirs." type="journal article" year="1831">Wied (1831: 710)</bibRefCitation>
, and says the 
<typeStatus box="[364,414,1326,1347]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
is in AMNH, probably basing this on Allen. AMNH 4352 remains in the 
<typeStatus box="[263,313,1385,1406]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
collection because it bears the 
<typeStatus box="[141,191,1414,1435]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
label added by Allen, but another label has been added to indicate that its status is unresolved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C." box="[122,325,1502,1524]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="7 - 53" refId="ref116079" refString="Dickinson, E. C. 2001. Systematic notes on Asian birds. 9. The '' Nouveau recueil de planches coloriees' ' of Temminck &amp; Laugier (1820 - 1839). Zoologische Verhandelingen 335: 7 - 53." type="journal article" year="2001">Dickinson (2001)</bibRefCitation>
has studied the publication dates of the various livraisons of Temminck and has shown that 1824 is the correct date for livraison 49.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[93,620,213,1759]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[262,405,1621,1642]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Conirostrum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[262,405,1621,1642]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="22">Conirostrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lowery, G. H., Jr. &amp; B. L. Monroe, Jr." box="[93,478,1649,1672]" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" pagination="3 - 93" refId="ref121834" refString="Lowery, G. H., Jr., and B. L. Monroe, Jr. 1968. Parulidae. In R. A. Paynter, Jr. (editor), Checklist of birds of the world, vol. 14: 3 - 93. Cambridge, MA: Museum of Comparative Zoology, 433 pp." type="book chapter" year="1968">Lowery and Monroe (1968: 82)</bibRefCitation>
as a genus incertae sedis in the 
<taxonomicName box="[345,460,1679,1701]" class="Aves" family="Parulidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Parulidae</taxonomicName>
. It is usually now included in the 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dickinson, 2003: 815)" baseAuthorityName="Dickinson" baseAuthorityPageNumber="815" baseAuthorityYear="2003" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
Thraupidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Dickinson, E. C." pageId="22" pageNumber="22" refId="ref116121" refString="Dickinson, E. C. (editor). 2003. The Howard and Moore complete checklist of the birds of the world, 3 rd ed. London: Christopher Helm, 1039 pp." type="book" year="2003">Dickinson, 2003: 815</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
